== 对健康的威胁 ==
二氧化硫具有酸性，可与空气中的其他物质反应，生成微小的亚硫酸盐和硫酸盐颗粒。当这些颗粒被吸入时，它们将聚集于肺部，是呼吸系统症状和疾病、呼吸困难，以及过早死亡的一个原因<ref name="health1">{{cite web  | language =en  | publisher =[[美国国家环保局|美国国家环保局]]  | title =Health and Environmental Impacts of SO2  | url =http://www.epa.gov/air/sulfurdioxide/  | accessdate =2008-12-18  | archive-date =2015-08-14  | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20150814185654/http://www.epa.gov/air/sulfurdioxide/  | dead-url =no  }}</ref>。如果与水混合，再与皮肤接触，便有可能发生冻伤。与眼睛接触时，会造成红肿和疼痛<ref name="ILO">{{cite web  | language =en  | publisher =[[国际劳工组织|国际劳工组织]]  | title =Sulphur Dioxide  | url =http://www.ilo.org/public/english/protection/safework/cis/products/icsc/dtasht/_icsc00/icsc0074.htm  | accessdate =2008-12-18  | archive-date =2009-04-18  | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20090418174741/http://www.ilo.org/public/english/protection/safework/cis/products/icsc/dtasht/_icsc00/icsc0074.htm  | dead-url =no  }}</ref>。

